            "id": 1,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "Norovirus is a major etiologic agent in worldwide outbreaks of gastroenteritis",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "associated with food as well as person - to - person transmission . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "The ubiquitous nature of Norovirus necessitates simple and rapid detection methods with high accuracy and sensitivity . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "To this end , several investigators have evaluated the usefulness of commercial reverse - transcription loop - mediated isothermal amplification ( RT - LAMP ) kits",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "for detecting Norovirus genogroups I ( GI ) and II ( GII ) . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "In previous studies , the conventional Loopamp kit for Norovirus GII showed a relatively high detection rate ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "while that for Norovirus GI showed a relatively low detection rate . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In the present study , clinical Norovirus specimens were used",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "to compare the detection rate of a modified Loopamp kit for Norovirus GI with the rates of the conventional Loopamp kit for Norovirus GI and an ' ' in - house ' ' RT - LAMP GI primer set , methods",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "which had a high detection rate . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "Results from the present study showed",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "that the modified Loopamp kit for Norovirus GI had a higher detection rate for two viral genotypes",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "( GI.3 , GI.11 ) . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "On comparison with an ' ' in - house ' ' GII primer set",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "using genotype GII.4 viruses",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "circulating recently ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "the detection rate by the Loopamp kit for Norovirus GII was found to be higher , with a 98 % detection rate . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "These results indicate the applicability of the modified LAMP kit for GI and the conventional LAMP kit for GII for detection of Noroviruses in clinical samples . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        }
    ]
